$ Oracle: Anti join

An *anti join* returns rows from the left table for which there are no corresponding rows in the right table.

sa:

  Unlike an anti join, a → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/join/semi[semi joins] returns a record from the left table if there is a corresponding record in the right table.

  Event 10102 switches off anti joins.

  The → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters[init parameter]
     • `always_anti_join`
     • `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/optimizer/extend_jppd_view_types`
